<section id="command-orientation">
<title>ORIENTATION</title>
<indexterm><primary>ORIENTATION</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>ORIENTATION</command></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Outputs a list, the turtle's [roll pitch heading] each in degrees.
It is important to <link linkend="understand-your-orientation-in-3D">understand your orientation in 3D</link>.
</para>

<para>
ORIENTATION is designed to run in <link linkend="command-perspective">PERSPECTIVE</link> mode.
When used in 2D modes, the roll and pitch outputs are zero.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<programlisting><userinput>PERSPECTIVE
SETORIENTATION [180 45 90]
SHOW ORIENTATION</userinput>
[180 45 90]
</programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>


